1.desc: Other allied Modifiers no longer Dodge or Break-fall; they gain Unyielding instead.
1.profile:
The fifth Mimir M.E.O.W. to be developed, she excels at cleaning and organizing.
A serious neat freak, she manages the logistics and cleaning system for the entire Aether Gazer building and is an expert cleaner herself.
1.story:
The fifth Mimir M.E.O.W. to be developed, she excels at cleaning and organizing.
A serious neat freak, she manages the logistics and cleaning system for the entire Aether Gazer building and is an expert cleaner herself.
However, she's impulsive and timid in nature and often spends her days making blunders and apologizing.

2.desc: Restores 3% HP of all teammates whenever a Dodge effect is triggered.
2.profile:
The sixth Mimir M.E.O.W. to be developed, she's an excellent culinary researcher that manages the Aether Gazer canteen.
She'll get angry if people aren't eating properly, but is always touched to receive praise for the good food.
2.story:
The sixth Mimir M.E.O.W. to be developed, she's an excellent culinary researcher that manages the Aether Gazer canteen.
Rumored to have been developed after people complained that the meals were too monotonous, her dream is to come up with a new dish every day so that everyone at Aether Gazer can know the joy of delicious food.
She'll get angry if people aren't eating properly, but is always touched to receive praise for the good food.

3.desc: Extends the duration of Modified Mode by 3 seconds.
3.profile:
The second Mimir M.E.O.W. to be developed, his computing power is also the closest to Mimir's.
He's currently with the Cryptics assisting Ookuninushi and Heimdall's research and recording massive amounts of experimental data.
3.story:
The second Mimir M.E.O.W. to be developed, his computing power is also the closest to Mimir's.
Contrary to the nasty-tempered Mimir, Mitir is more like the expected Mimir design—reticent, but always completing tasks assigned by headquarters to the letter.
He's currently with the Cryptics assisting Ookuninushi and Heimdall's research and recording massive amounts of experimental data.

4.desc: The team leader gains corresponding Combat Resources (20 Rage, 20 Energy, 1 Trace, or 20 Divine Grace) whenever another allied Modifier's Dodge effect is triggered.
4.profile:
The fourth Mimir M.E.O.W. to be developed, this is the noisiest of all the models.
He plays rhythmic music wherever he goes, always bobbing his head to the beat. Even his voice has an electronic cadence.
4.story:
The fourth Mimir M.E.O.W. to be developed, he’s the noisiest of all M.E.O.Ws.
He plays rhythmic music wherever he goes, always bobbing his head to the beat. Even his voice has an electronic cadence.
He manages all of Aether Gazer's audio and visual products and seems to tend towards dexterity and high mobility tactics when engaged in combat as an auxiliary AI.

5.desc: When the Modifying Level is at Ω, increases other allied Modifiers' Crit Rates by 10%, and increases the Ultimate Skill charge by 1% whenever their attacks crit.
5.profile: The tenth Mimir M.E.O.W. to be developed, unlike all his predecessors, Mininja has particular combat functions. Shy and introverted, he usually refers to himself in the most humble of terms.
5.story:
The tenth Mimir M.E.O.W. to be developed, unlike all his predecessors, Mininja has particular combat functions. Shy and introverted, he usually refers to himself in the most humble of terms.
Developed to go to Sasanami to carry out special missions for the Pheasant Squad, his design is a reference to the ancient profession of "Prowlers" found in Sasanami. Many of Kuninotokotachi's opinions were taken into account in the design stage.
It's worth mentioning that Mininja's reconnaissance and counter-reconnaissance capabilities have been enhanced and his entire body is made from special material capable of invisibility. Not only can he disappear from the line of sight of the naked eye for long periods of time, even infrared or heat-sensing instruments will have a tough time detecting him.

6.desc: Restores other allied Modifiers to their full HP when they take fatal damage, but decreases their damage and healing effects by 10% for the rest of the battle when the effect is triggered; stacks up to 5 times.
6.profile:
The third Mimir M.E.O.W. to be developed, she has a rare feminine personality.
Designed with consideration for the failure that allowed Mimir to become an overbearing dweeb, Mimtastic is an amalgam of all of humanity's good qualities.
6.story:
The third Mimir M.E.O.W. to be developed, she has a rare feminine personality.
Designed with consideration for the failure that allowed Mimir to become an overbearing dweeb, Mimtastic is an amalgam of all of humanity's good qualities.
Like a big sister to the Modifiers and Administrator, she's more concerned about everyone's safety than the success of the battle. She'll even concern herself with the smallest things in the crew's day-to-day lives and has been described as an "angel of goodness" by all.
She calls Mimir "big brother" and will stand up for the newcomers he bullies, so they're always getting into scraps. Relatively serious, she always wrests the upper hand from the trouble-averse Mimir.
Her data processing abilities on the weaker side, she frequents the training room, cafeteria, and game room to remind everyone not to overdo it, to eat three meals a day, and to sleep and rise early.

109305.desc:
An allied Jin-ei - Kuninotokotachi will preferentially cast a Ninjutsu skill that's different to the last one.
When the Aether Code: Genesis - Way of Ninja is activated: If her Wind DMG is no less than her Thunder DMG when she enters the battlefield, she will cast Rain of Kunai, Razer Whirlwind and Tectonic Blast one by one repeatedly. If her Wind DMG is lower than her Thunder DMG when she enters the battlefield, she will cast Tectonic Blast, Wondrous Thunder and Rain of Kunai one by one repeatedly.
109305.title: <color=#909090>"A good ninja always keeps their opponent guessing." </color>

109306.desc: An allied Jin-ei - Kuninotokotachi will cast Razer Whirlwind only if her Wind DMG is no less than her Thunder DMG when she enters the battlefield. If her Wind DMG is lower than her Thunder DMG when she enters the battlefield, she will cast Wondrous Thunder only.
109306.title: <color=#909090>"Move as the wind, and strike as lightning." </color>
109306.profile: When she is a teammate, Jin-ei - Kuninotokotachi will prioritize casting Wondrous Thunder and Razer Whirlwind.

109307.desc: An allied Jin-ei - Kuninotokotachi will cast Rain of Kunai only if her Physical DMG is no less than her Fire DMG when she enters the battlefield. If her Physical DMG is lower than her Fire DMG when she enters the battlefield, she will cast Tectonic Blast only.
109307.title: <color=#909090>"No enemy can escape from a trap that anticipates their every move." </color>
